{
  "stem": "25178.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in his dismissal, he wrote in the papers that it would be-- it would be unfair to the defendant to have a trial after trial by the state.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The state has unlimited funds, and it would be a financial burden on the defendant.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was the end of the trial.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He never got another trial.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He never got thrown out of the Air Force, because it happened off the base and the Air Force said it's a civil case, we can't do anything about it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wrote letters to the Air Force.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's nothing they can do about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he got no punishments whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The only punishment he got was his wife divorced him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 15 SECONDS] Yeah, that was in 1979, and we have been trying to rebuild our lives ever since.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We have some happy times now.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Karen getting married to a good husband, a beautiful grandchild.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Olivia getting married to a good husband, beautiful grandson.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For that I have to thank my wife, Juliet, because she introduced me, when I met her, to the Jewish life-- not religion, the Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She-- her family was not a very religious family, either, but her sister married a very religious man, and through him, because of him, the whole family went towards going from the traditional more toward the religious part.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now are there-- are there things that you do as a family that are more traditional and Jewish?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, we go to shul more often, and Juliet has a kosher kitchen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] We celebrate the holidays, Yom Kippur, Rosh Hashanah, Hanukkah.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Both of the children went to private Jewish schools.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
